CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1953, pg. 6, reads: "Art Award Winner Congratulated - Raymond Saunders, Schenley High student, who won two art contest awards and a scholarship at the National High School Art Exhibitions, is shown being congratulated by M. R. Robinson, publisher of Scholastic magazines, sponsors of the annual competitions. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: M. R. Robinson on right presenting award to Raymond "Ray" Saunders, at National High School Art Exhibition
